          <title type="preferred">Ācāryastavarājabhūṣaṇa </title>
          <editor key="p_4" role="aut">Rāmabhadra Dīkṣita</editor>
          <editor key="p_27" role="hnr">Kṛṣṇānanda Sarasvatī</editor>
          <note type="genre">Hymn</note>
          <note type="subject" source="other">A hymn commemorating the hymn of Rāmabhadra’s co-pupil Brahmānanda Sarasvatī (titled Ācāryastavarāja), which honours their preceptor Kṛṣṇānanda Sarasvatī.</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Stavamaṇimālā, Sarasvatī Vilāsa Series 6</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">NCC vol. 15, 97; vol. 2, 38; vol. 24, 188</note>
          <note type="bibliographical">Adyar vol. 1, 188a (2 mss.)</note>
          <note type="general">One of the 9 hymns that are printed in the Stavamaṇimālā as Sarasvatī Vilāsa Series 6 (ed. Subrahmanya Sastri)</note>
          <note type="general">See Thiruvengadathan pg. 17 and Raghavan introduction to Śāhendravilāsa pg. 41</note>
          <note type="general">126 verses in Śārdūlavikrīḍita metre (see Sinhā 311–312)</note>
        </bibl>
      </listBibl>
